  <prompt>
    Remove the hardcoded `ChatSummarizePlaybookId` GUID at `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs:78-79` (`44285d15-...`) and migrate the orchestrator to resolve the playbook by stable code `summarize-document-chat` via the `/by-code/{code}` endpoint or direct `IPlaybookLookupService`. Per spec FR-05 this is the FIRST stable-code migration (lowest blast radius — no config override exists today).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat-routing layer + minimal-API DI.</role>

  <goal>
    `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.ChatSummarizePlaybookId` constant removed. Playbook resolved by stable code `summarize-document-chat` (lifted to typed options or direct `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByCodeAsync`). Integration test confirms `/api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize` continues to work end-to-end with same output. Telemetry "path" dimension on `R5SummarizeTelemetry` unchanged.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec.md §1.7 Pattern A + FR-05. `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` is the chat /summarize convergence point (per R6 FR-26). It has no config override today — purely hardcoded GUID — which makes it both: (a) lowest blast radius (no env-specific config to maintain), and (b) the riskiest if migration regresses (no fallback). Tests cover the convergence invariant; do not weaken.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs</file>
