  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs:78-79` — locate `ChatSummarizePlaybookId` constant.</step>
    <step order="2">Identify the playbook lookup call site that uses this constant; trace the flow to understand what shape the orchestrator needs (GUID? Entity? Code?).</step>
    <step order="3">Choose migration shape:
      (a) Lift to `WorkspaceOptions.SummarizeChatPlaybookCode = "summarize-document-chat"` typed option; OR
      (b) Directly use `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByCodeAsync("summarize-document-chat", tenantId)` per ADR-018 preference.
      Document choice in PR.</step>
    <step order="4">Replace hardcoded GUID + code path with code-based resolution.</step>
    <step order="5">Update unit tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/` — fixtures should use stable code.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify telemetry "path" dimension on `R5SummarizeTelemetry` unchanged (spec.md §1.5 mentioned).</step>
    <step order="7">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Must pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Run integration test for `/api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize`. Must pass.</step>
    <step order="9">Measure BFF publish size; report delta.</step>
    <step order="10">code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 quality gates).</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 014 → ✅; current-task.md → task 015 ready.</step>
  </steps>

